<chapter xml:id="Chapter-Systems-of-Linear-Equations" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Systems of Linear Equations</title>

  <p>
    After completing this chapter, students should be able to do the following.
  </p>

  <objectives>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Solve systems of linear equations using Gauss-Jordan elimination to reduce to echelon form.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Interpret existence and uniqueness of solutions geometrically.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Compute the rank of a matrix using Gaussian elimination.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Implement Jacobi's method and the Gauss-Seidel method to solve linear systems.
                </p>
            </li> 
        </ul>
</objectives>

